The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Manoj happy after meeting Dalmiya
                                                                                                                                                                                                       Manoj happy after meeting Dalmiya
            A STAFF REPORTER            Tiwary                           
	Calcutta: Manoj Tiwary may finally stay with Bengal during the forthcoming season. After a one-on-one with newly-elected CAB president Jagmohan Dalmiya on Thursday, Manoj said that he will decide within a couple of days.         
	The meeting was arranged by an influential official, and Manoj was happy with the outcome. The middle-order batsman has been in talks with Rajasthan and Saurashtra and had more or less made up his mind to switch loyalties.         
	He is very happy and returned satisfied. He wants to stay with Bengal, said a source.         
	Manoj has reportedly got a lucrative offer from Rajasthan, though he didnt want to comment on it.         
	I am happy with todays meeting I will let them know about my plans within a couple of days, Manoj said later.                                                                                                                          
